    <thetext>Description of problem:
ibus-libzhuyin has been proposed to be the default input method for Chinese (Taiwan). I have installed a fresh Fedora 24 (f25 also) in Chinese (Taiwan) language and found some problems in setup.

Problems:
1. gnome-initial-setup only lists &quot;chewing&quot; (ibus-chewing).
2. the default input method for Chinese (Taiwan) language since Fedora 24 is &quot;New Zhuyin&quot; (ibus-libzhuyin). ibus-libzhuyin is installed by default, but not listed in the setup dialog.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
gnome-desktop3-3.22.2-1.fc25.x86_64

How reproducible:
Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. First login into a fresh user using Chinese (Taiwan) (zh_TW) locale
2. Set input method for Chinese (Taiwan) in the gnome-initial-setup dialog

Actual results:
1. &quot;chewing&quot; is the only available input method listed

Expected results:
1. &quot;New Zhuyin&quot; (libzhuyin) is the only available input method listed.

Additional info:
Related Bug - https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1405709</thetext>
